      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "REEL CRYSTAL (4) coming along nicely as she gets out in trip and looks to find a winning race today. Gave her all with a gritty head second over 2000m at Wagga on a heavy (9) surface. Stable apprentice sticks and has the upside to get the job done. CHARLOTTING (7) on the two-day back-up when she jumped in trip with a comfortable victory as fav over 1800m at Gulgong. Finds a tougher race but looks well placed with Stiff's claim. FARRAIGE (8) outclassed at Canterbury and Hawkesbury at his last two outings and back to his grade for this. Lone victory came at this track and trip and can take a hand in the finish. LUCKY STAR (3) went back early and failed to make an impression when tenth over 1800m at Hawkesbury in BM64 class. Can get the trip with the 59.5kg.",
